guide.tool.oreville_wb:albzqmh.rlbnkvl=While the Block Picker is in Addition Mode, every block you select will be added to your existing palette. To revert to a single block, re-open this menu, and select Disable Addition Mode.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:brush=Brushes can do all sorts of things to the world depending on the type made. Just use it and watch how the area in front of you gets affected.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:igfnerr_selection_wand=The Classic Selection Wand is used to create selections; an area of the world you want to edit using World Builder. Press §cAttack / Destroy§7 on a block to mark the first position, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 on another block to mark the second.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:clear_mask=The Clear Mask item clears any mask set with the Mask Picker. To use it: Press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to clear your mask.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:aokhmde_qwaonln=The Scale Clipboard item scales your clipboard from the ground up. To use it, create a selection using the Selection Wand, make a copy using the Copy or Cut item, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to choose how much to scale your selection.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:hykhqxz_toolbox=The Toolbox is a portable chest in your inventory, containing all the items World Builder provides. To open it: press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to get all the items World Builder provides.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:command=The §cCommand Tool§7 runs a Minecraft command when you use it. For example, using say Hi! will print the words "Hi!" in the chat, when used. If you use the tool on a block, it will run the command at that block's face.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:config=The World Builder Settings item is used to access a settings menu for World Builder. To use it: Press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to open the options menu, adjust the settings to your preference, then press §cSave Changes§7 to update your settings. A detailed breakdown of all the settings can be found in the Handbook.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:osaxmlj=The Copy item creates a copy of your current selection and stores it in your clipboard. To use it, make a selection with the Selection Wand, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to copy your selection.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:cut=The Cut item deletes anything in your current selection and stores it in your clipboard. To use it, make a selection using the Selection Wand, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to cut your selection.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:cycler=The §cCycler Tool§7 cycles through the state of the block you interact with. You can change what state you are changing by hitting the block.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:draw_dvtnraj=The Draw Cone item draws a cone of a selected size. To use it: pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker, Press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 on any block to set the centre point of the pyramid, move your courser or player to set the size of the cone, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to draw your pyramid.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:draw_yewycgr=The Draw Curve item draws a curve of blocks among several points. To use it: pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker, press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 on any block to set that block as the first point of the curve, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 on other blocks along the curve. Do it twice at the last point to finish drawing the curve.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:draw_sdtkvvx=The Draw Cylinder item draws a cylinder of a selected size. To use it: pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker, Press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 on any block to set the centre point of the cylinder, move your courser or player to set the size of the cylinder, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to draw your cylinder.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:draw_bphvufz=The Draw Dome item draws a dome of a selected size, and opposite of the direction you're facing. To use it: pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker, Press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 on any block to set the centre point of the sphere, move your courser or player to set the size of the sphere, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to draw your sphere.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:draw_xjrgsar=The Draw Ellipsoid item draws an ellipsoid of selected dimensions. To use it: pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker, Press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 on any block to set the centre point of the sphere, move your courser or player to set the size of the sphere, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to draw your sphere.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:draw_oraynum=The Draw Line item draws a line of blocks between two selected points. To use it: pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker, press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 on any block to set that block as the first point of the line, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 on any other block to draw your line. 	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:draw_pyramid=The Draw Pyramid item draws a pyramid of a selected size. To use it: pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker, Press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 on any block to set the centre point of the pyramid, move your courser or player to set the size of the pyramid, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to draw your pyramid.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:draw_krlvkqp=The Draw Sphere item draws a sphere of a selected size. To use it: pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker, Press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 on any block to set the centre point of the sphere, move your courser or player to set the size of the sphere, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to draw your sphere.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:draw_tools=§aThere are other shapes you can draw, too! Just Sneak and Use Item / Place Block with the item in your hand to switch to other shapes.§r	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:draw_nvctyzp=The Draw Torus item draws a torus of a selected size. To use it: pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker, Press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 on any block to set the centre point of the torus, move your courser or player to set the size of the torus, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to draw your torus.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:aslntmx=The §cExtruder Tool§7 will take any block you interact with, along with surrounding of the same type, and extrude them out towards you. You can also specify whether to dig into the blocks instead.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:ucawkdg_selection_wand=The Far Selection Wand is used to create selections; an area of the world you want to edit using World Builder. Press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 towards a far away block to mark your first or second position.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:fill=The §cFill Tool§7 will create a flood of a certain palette of blocks where you use it. If it's done under something, it will stop at any "holes" automatically.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:lghzamp=The Flip item flips your clipboard across the direction you are facing. To use it, create a selection using the Selection Wand, make a copy using the Copy or Cut item, face the direction you want to flip across, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to flip your selection.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:mask_picker=The Mask Picker, limits World Builder items to only work on a selected block. To use it: press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 on any block to set it as your mask. 	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:navigation_wand=The Navigation Wand teleports you to any block you are looking at. To use it: Look at a block you would like to teleport to, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to teleport.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:open_toolbox=The toolbox replaces your entire inventory with World Builder tools. You can return to your normal inventory by closing the toolbox.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:paste=The Paste item pastes a copy of your clipboard into the world. To use it, create a selection using the Selection Wand, make a copy using the Copy or Cut item, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to paste your selection.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:pattern_picker=The Block Picker selects which block other items in World Builder will use. To use it press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 on any block you would like to use.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:redo=The Redo item will restore the last action undone by the Undo item. To use it: press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to restore your last undo.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:replacer=The §cReplacer Tool§7 replaces blocks you interact with, to another block. After creating the tool, you can still change what block is created by hitting the block of your choice.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:cwyutyy_endgdbf=The Advanced Rotation item lets you rotate your clipboard in any angle; including along the x and z axes.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:cwyutyy_emzxhzu=The Rotate Anti-Clockwise item rotates your clipboard anti-clockwise by 90°. To use it, create a selection using the Selection Wand, make a copy with the Copy or Cut item, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to rotate your selection.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:cwyutyy_mwhykoq=The Rotate Clockwise item rotates your clipboard clockwise by 90°. To use it, create a selection using the Selection Wand, make a copy with the Copy or Cut item, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to rotate your selection.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:xlqziah=The Ruler item is used to display information about your current Selection. It can also place down marker blocks to help you space out your designs. To use it, create a Selection using the Selection Wand. Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while holding the Ruler item. Select how many markers you want to see using the slider and press submit.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:mqigbya_command=Use this tool to run any World Builder command. A detailed breakdown of all of them can be found in the Handbook.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:selection_oestvsz=The Expand Mode expands/contracts your Selection bounds. To use it, create a Selection using the Selection Wand. Face the direction you want to affect and press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button with the Expand item in your hand. Pick the amount you want to go and whether to expand or contract and Save.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:selection_fill=The Selection Fill item fills your selection with any block you have selected with the Block Picker. To use it, create a selection using the Selection Wand, pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to fill your selection.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:selection_move=The Selection Move item moves a selection by a set amount of blocks, in the direction you are facing. To use it, create a selection using the Selection Wand, face the direction you would like to move your selection, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to open the move menu.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:selection_outline=The Selection Outline item, outlines your selection with any block you have selected with the Block Picker, creating a hollow cube. To use it, create a selection using the Selection Wand, pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to outline your selection.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:selection_lgddqvp=The Replace Mode changes specified blocks in your Selection with blocks you have picked using the Block Picker. To use it, create a Selection using the Selection Wand. Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button with the Replace item in your hand. Pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker. Select a block you would like to replace with the Mask Picker. Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button with the Green Tick item in your hand to update your Selection.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:selection_bushrfh=The Selection Smooth item, smoothes the height of blocks in your selection. The more iterations, the smoother the result.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:selection_stack=The Selection Stack item will duplicate your selection and place it in a row towards the direction you are facing. To use it: create a selection using the Selection Wand, face the direction you would like to stack your selection, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to open the stack menu.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:selection_tools=§aThere are other operations you can perform with the Selection Tool. just hold Sneak and press Use Item / Place Block with the Selection item in your hand to open the Selection Tools menu.§r	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:selection_wall=The Selection Wall item creates a wall around your selection with any block you have selected with the Block Picker. To use it, create a selection using the Selection Wand, pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker, then press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to create a wall around your selection.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:selection_wand=The Selection Wand is used to create selections; an area of the world you want to edit using World Builder. Press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 on a block to start creating your selection, then do it again at another location to complete it. You can also use the tool on the complete selection to expand and contract it.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:selection_wand.ldqyjnz=Keep New Wand	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:selection_wand.pjptvqh=Revert to Old Wand	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:stacker=The §cStacker Tool§7 will take any block you interact with, and make a column in the direction you're facing. You can specify an optional mask to configure what blocks will be replaced.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:tool_brush_config=The Tool Brush Manager is used to create and manage your own tools and brushes. To use it: press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to open the options menu, from here you can create new brushes and tools, and manage existing ones.	#
guide.tool.oreville_wb:undo=The Undo item will undo the last action performed using world builder. To use it: press §cUse Item / Place Block§7 to undo your last edit. 	#
