ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.1=The Blob Brush creates a mis-shaped sphere or Blob!	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.yjcqsdz=9. §7Select any block using the Block Picker.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.uiwhyvv=10. §7Create an optional mask for this Blob Brush using the Mask Picker.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.qrwzkpp=11. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while holding the Confirm item to open an options menu.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.fanfouf=12. §7Write a name for your Brush in the §cName§7 field.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.qpksasl=13. §7Press the §cSave Changes§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.vrqpxni=Your Blob Brush will now be in your inventory.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.xclccmg=To use the Blob Brush:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.hqtfelu=1. §7Point your crosshair where you would like your Blob to appear.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.iyanacu=2. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while holding a Blob Brush.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.fpdlmcv=A Blob will now be created at your target point.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.2=To Create a Blob Brush:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.xdnvfuf=While holding a Blob brush a preview of your Blob will appear. 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.vjnannn=Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§r button while §cSneaking§r to adjust the brushes settings.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.fqzcsma=Congratulations! You have now learned all of the basics of the World Builder Add-On. Get comfortable with these and then consider checking out our advanced guides on the Command Tool and the Whitelist settings.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.3=1. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while holding the Tool Brush Manager to open an options menu.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.4=2. §7Press the §c+ New Brush§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.5=3. §7Press the §cBlob Brush§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.6=4. §7Move the §cSize §7slider to adjust the size of your Blob§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.7=5. §7Move the §cGrowth Percentage §7slider to adjust the volume of blocks in your Blob§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.8=7. §7Move the §cSmoothness §7slider to adjust the smoothness of your Blob§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.vfpwhsl.9=8. §7Press the §cSave Changes§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.cqyoonn_brush.jptaeut=Blob Brush	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.seeizvr_cycler_tool.vfpwhsl.1=The Block Cycler Tool cycles through a blocks available block states.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.seeizvr_cycler_tool.vfpwhsl.yjcqsdz=- §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while holding a Block Cycler Tool on any block that has multiple states.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.seeizvr_cycler_tool.vfpwhsl.uiwhyvv=The state of the block will now be cycled.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.seeizvr_cycler_tool.vfpwhsl.qrwzkpp=With all of the Custom Tools looked at we'll move on now to the Custom Brushes.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.seeizvr_cycler_tool.vfpwhsl.2=To create a Block Cycler Tool:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.seeizvr_cycler_tool.vfpwhsl.3=1. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while holding the Tool Brush Manager to open an options menu.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.seeizvr_cycler_tool.vfpwhsl.4=2. §7Press the §c+ New Tool§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.seeizvr_cycler_tool.vfpwhsl.5=3. §7Press the §cBlock Replacer Tool§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.seeizvr_cycler_tool.vfpwhsl.6=4. §7Write a name for your tool in the §cName§7 Field.§r	#
