ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_vioteqj_oraynum.vfpwhsl.1=The Draw Curve item, allows you to create a curved line by selecting several points.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_vioteqj_oraynum.vfpwhsl.2=To use the Draw Curve item:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_vioteqj_oraynum.vfpwhsl.3=1. §7Pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_vioteqj_oraynum.vfpwhsl.4=2. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block §7button on any block with the Draw Curve item in your hand. This will set that block as the first point of the line.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_vioteqj_oraynum.vfpwhsl.5=3. §7Repeat step two to set the other points on your line. You may place these points on blocks or in the air.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_vioteqj_oraynum.vfpwhsl.6=4. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block §7button twice on on any block or in the air to set the last point of your line.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_vioteqj_oraynum.vfpwhsl.7=After the first point is selected a preview of your line will appear while holding the Draw Line item.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_vioteqj_oraynum.vfpwhsl.8=With out lines drawn, we'll move onto the rest of the Shape Tools.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_vioteqj_oraynum.jptaeut=Draw Curve	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_oraynum.vfpwhsl.1=The Draw Line item, draws a line of blocks between two selected points.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_oraynum.vfpwhsl.2=To use the Draw Line item:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_oraynum.vfpwhsl.3=1. §7Pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_oraynum.vfpwhsl.4=2. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button on any block with the Draw Line item in your hand. This will set that block as the first point of the line.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_oraynum.vfpwhsl.5=3. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button on any other block. This will set that block as the second point of the line.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_oraynum.vfpwhsl.6=A line will now be drawn between the two points you selected.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_oraynum.vfpwhsl.7=After the first point is selected a preview of your line will appear while holding the Draw Line item. 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_oraynum.vfpwhsl.8=The second point can also be set by pressing the §cUse Item / Place Block§r button while not looking at a block. This will set the point to where you are standing. Useful for creating lines in midair. 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_oraynum.vfpwhsl.9=Now thay we have the basics down with the Draw Line, lets take a look at creating a Curve.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_oraynum.jptaeut=Draw Line	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.vfpwhsl.1=The Draw Sphere, Ellipsoid, Cylinder, Dome, Torus, Pyramid and Cone options, draw a shape of blocks of a selected size and can be accessed from the Draw Line tool.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.vfpwhsl.yjcqsdz=8. §7Press the Use Item / Place Block button again to place the shape.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.vfpwhsl.uiwhyvv=A shape will now be drawn at the size you selected.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.vfpwhsl.qrwzkpp=*Extra Settings	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.vfpwhsl.fanfouf=1. §7Hollowness - Defines the thickness of the walls. The higher the value the more hollow space in the shape/less thick walls.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.vfpwhsl.qpksasl=2. §7Hollow Wall Placement - Determines if a wall is placed from Inside -> Outside or Outside -> Inside.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.vfpwhsl.vrqpxni=3. §7Placement - Choose whether to draw your shape from the center or from the surface the shape is attached to.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.vfpwhsl.xclccmg=Now that we can draw shapes, in the next section we will learn about the Navigation Wand.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.vfpwhsl.2=To use these items:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.vfpwhsl.3=1. §7Pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.vfpwhsl.4=2. §7Hold the Draw Line Tool.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.vfpwhsl.5=3. §7Hold §cSneak/Fly Down§7 and press §cUse Item / Place Block§7.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.vfpwhsl.6=4. §7Select the shape you wish to draw§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.vfpwhsl.7=5. §7Adjust the Extra Settings* menu to a point you are happy with.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.vfpwhsl.8=6. §7Press the Use Item / Place Block button on any block with one of the items in your hand. This will set that block as the centre point of the shape.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.vfpwhsl.9=7. §7Move your crosshair or player away from the centre point to set how large you want the shape.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.draw_orsspld.jptaeut=Draw Shape	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.1=The Terrain Brush is used to morph terrain at a distance using different modes.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.yjcqsdz=- Fill: §7Fills holes in the terrain.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.uiwhyvv=- Melt: §7Expands existing holes in the terrain.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.qrwzkpp=- Smooth: §7Smooths holes and rises in the terrain, creating a smooth surface.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.fanfouf=6. §7Press the §cSave Changes§7 Button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.qpksasl=7. §7Create an optional mask for this Terrain Brush using the Mask Picker.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.vrqpxni=8. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while holding the Confirm item to open an options menu.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.xclccmg=9. §7Write a name for your Brush in the §cName§7 field.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.hqtfelu=10. §7Press the §cSave Changes§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.iyanacu=Your Terrain Brush will now be in your inventory.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.fpdlmcv=To use the Terrain Brush:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.2=To create a Terrain Brush:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.xdnvfuf=1. §7Point your crosshair where you would like to morph your terrain.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.vjnannn=2. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while holding the Terrain Brush.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.fqzcsma=The terrain at your crosshair will now be morphed.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.flzitzb=While holding a Terrain Brush a preview of the are area to be morphed will appear.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.aiqkzuo=Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§r button while §cSneaking§r to adjust the brushes settings.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.usmrjbn=Next we'll look at the Overlay Brush.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.3=1. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while holding the Tool Brush Manager to open an options menu.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.4=2. §7Press the §c+ New Brush§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.5=3. §7Press the §cTerrain Brush§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.6=4. §7Move the §cSize§7 slider to the size of area you would like to erode.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.7=5. §7Select which Erosion Type you would like to use from the dropdown menu:§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.8=- Erode: §7Destroys blocks creating holes in the terrain.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.vfpwhsl.9=- Lift: §7Pulls blocks outwards making rises in the terrain.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xyieqjj_brush.jptaeut=Terrain Brush	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.aslntmx_tool.vfpwhsl.1=The Extruder Tool adds or subtracts a layer of blocks from a surface.	#
