ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.fgxsvbm.vfpwhsl.1=Welcome to §eWorld Builder§r! With this Add-On you can move blocks, paint, sculpt terrain, and much more!	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.fgxsvbm.vfpwhsl.2=To get started, press the §cGive Toolbox§r button in the World Builder Handbook. Open the Toolbox to get all your new tools, and start building!	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.fgxsvbm.vfpwhsl.3=Manage your Tools, Brushes, and general settings with the World Builder Settings item.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.fgxsvbm.jptaeut=Introduction	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.vfpwhsl.1=The Mask Picker, limits World Builder items to only work on selected blocks.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.vfpwhsl.yjcqsdz=Any blocks you select will now be added onto your mask palette instead of replacing it. 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.vfpwhsl.uiwhyvv=To return to one block mode:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.vfpwhsl.qrwzkpp=1. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while §cSneaking§7 to open an additional options menu.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.vfpwhsl.fanfouf=2. §7Press the §cDisable Addition Mode§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.vfpwhsl.qpksasl=3. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button on any block you would like to add to your mask palette.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.vfpwhsl.vrqpxni=Your mask palette will now be overwritten by the newly selected block, removing any previously selected blocks.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.vfpwhsl.xclccmg=With a mask picked we'll now take a look at how to clear it. 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.vfpwhsl.2=This item prevents World Builder from working on unselected blocks. This can appear as broken functionality. Use the Clear Mask item to clear your masks, re-enabling world builder to work on all blocks.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.vfpwhsl.3=To use the Mask Picker:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.vfpwhsl.4=- §7While holding the Mask Picker, press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button on any block you would like to add to your Mask palette.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.vfpwhsl.5=That block will now be selected, limiting other items in World Builder to only work on that block. 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.vfpwhsl.6=By default only one block can be selected at a time. 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.vfpwhsl.7=To add additional blocks to your mask palette:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.vfpwhsl.8=1. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while §cSneaking§7 to open an additional options menu.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.vfpwhsl.9=2. §7Press the §cEnable Addition Mode§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mask_picker.jptaeut=Mask Picker	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.navigation_wand.vfpwhsl.1=The Navigation Wand teleports you to any block you are looking at.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.navigation_wand.vfpwhsl.2=To use the Navigation Wand:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.navigation_wand.vfpwhsl.3=1. §7Look at a block you would like to teleport to.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.navigation_wand.vfpwhsl.4=2. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while holding the Navigation Wand.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.navigation_wand.vfpwhsl.5=The Navigation Wand cannot teleport you into unloaded chunks.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.navigation_wand.vfpwhsl.6=With the gift of teleportation mastered we'll go back to looking at our selection with the Ruler Tool.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.navigation_wand.jptaeut=Navigation Wand	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.1=The Overlay Brush replaces the surface of terrain at a distance	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.yjcqsdz=8. §7Create an optional mask for this Overlay Brush using the Mask Picker.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.uiwhyvv=9. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while holding the Confirm item to open an options menu.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.qrwzkpp=10. §7Write a name for your Brush in the §cName§7 field.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.fanfouf=11. §7Press the §cSave Changes§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.qpksasl=Your Overlay Brush will now be in your inventory.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.vrqpxni=To use the Overlay Brush:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.xclccmg=1. §7Point your crosshair where you would like to replace the surface of your terrain.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.hqtfelu=2. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while holding the Overlay Brush.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.iyanacu=The surface of the terrain at your crosshair will now be replaced with your picked block.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.fpdlmcv=While holding an Overlay Brush a preview of the area to be replaced will appear. 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.2=To create an Overlay Brush:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.xdnvfuf=Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§r button while §cSneaking§r to adjust the brushes settings.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.vjnannn=Finally we'll look at the Blob Brush.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.3=1. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while holding the Tool Brush Manager to open an options menu.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.4=2. §7Press the §c+ New Brush§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.5=3. §7Press the §cOverlay Brush§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.6=4. §7Move the §cSize§7 slider to the size of area you would like to erode.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.7=5. §7Move to §cDepth§7 slider to how many blocks below the surface of the terrain you would like to replace.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.8=6. §7Press the §cSave Changes§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.vfpwhsl.9=7. §7Select any block using the Block Picker.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.overlay_brush.jptaeut=Overlay Brush	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.vfpwhsl.1=The Paste item pastes a copy of your clipboard into the world.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.vfpwhsl.yjcqsdz=1. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while §cSneaking§7 to open an options menu.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.vfpwhsl.uiwhyvv=2. §7Press the §cToggle Selection Updating§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.vfpwhsl.qrwzkpp=The Paste Item can also be used to flip and rotate your clipboard in the same way as the dedicated Flip and Rotate items.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.vfpwhsl.fanfouf=To do this:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.vfpwhsl.qpksasl=1. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while §cSneaking§7 to open an options menu.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.vfpwhsl.vrqpxni=2. §7Press the §cFlip§7, §cRotate Clockwise§7 or §cRotate Anti-Clockwise§7 buttons.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.vfpwhsl.xclccmg=Pasted something where it shouldn't go? Want to move a build you already have? We'll look at the Cut tool next.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.vfpwhsl.2=To use the Paste item: 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.vfpwhsl.3=1. §7Create a selection using the Selection Wand.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.vfpwhsl.4=2. §7Make a copy of your selection using either the Copy or Cut item.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.vfpwhsl.5=3. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while holding the Paste item.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.vfpwhsl.6=Your copied selection will now be pasted into the world. 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.vfpwhsl.7=A preview of your copied selection will appear while holding the Paste item. The position of this preview is set by where you were standing when you made the copy. 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.vfpwhsl.8=By default your current selection will be updated to select the pasted clipboard when the Paste item is used.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.vfpwhsl.9=To change this:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.paste.jptaeut=Paste	#
