ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xlqziah.vfpwhsl.1=The Ruler item is used to display information about your current selection. It can also place down marker blocks to help you space out your designs. 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xlqziah.vfpwhsl.2=To use the Ruler item:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xlqziah.vfpwhsl.3=1. §7Create a selection using the Selection Wand.§r 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xlqziah.vfpwhsl.4=2. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block §7button while holding the Ruler item.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xlqziah.vfpwhsl.5=3. §7Select how many markers you want to see using the slider§r 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xlqziah.vfpwhsl.6=4. §7Press submit.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xlqziah.vfpwhsl.7=You will now see the volume of your selection and the block width, length and depth displayed on screen along with the selected number of marker blocks in your selection.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xlqziah.vfpwhsl.8=Next we will look at Undo and Redo.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.xlqziah.jptaeut=Ruler	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mqigbya_command.vfpwhsl.1=The command system is an advanced feature of World Builder which allows players to execute tool functions via commands. These commands must be made within the Run Command tool as they will not execute if typed into game chat. 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mqigbya_command.vfpwhsl.2=Check out the sections below to see the commands for each operation.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.mqigbya_command.jptaeut=Run Command Tool (Advanced)	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.qwaonln_aokhmde.vfpwhsl.1=The Scale Clipboard item allows you to increase the size of your clipboard by up to a factor of 8.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.qwaonln_aokhmde.vfpwhsl.yjcqsdz=Well done, you now know how to use all of the Clipboard Tools! Next, we will look at the Selection Operations, starting with the Block Picker.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.qwaonln_aokhmde.vfpwhsl.2=To use the Scale Clipboard item:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.qwaonln_aokhmde.vfpwhsl.3=1. §7Create a selection using the §cSelection Wand§7.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.qwaonln_aokhmde.vfpwhsl.4=2. §7Make a copy of your selection using either the §cCopy §7or §cCut §7item.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.qwaonln_aokhmde.vfpwhsl.5=3. §7While holding the Scale Clipboard item press the §cUse Item / Place Block §7button.§r 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.qwaonln_aokhmde.vfpwhsl.6=4. §7Use the §cAmount §7slider to select the amount you want to increase you clipboard scale by.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.qwaonln_aokhmde.vfpwhsl.7=5. §7Select §cSave Changes§7.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.qwaonln_aokhmde.vfpwhsl.8=Your clipboard will now be scaled. To see the effect of this item, paste your clipboard using the Paste item.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.qwaonln_aokhmde.vfpwhsl.9=A preview of your clipboard will appear while holding the Scale Clipboard item. The position of this preview is set by where you were standing when you made the copy.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.qwaonln_aokhmde.jptaeut=Scale Clipboard	#
