ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_oestvsz.vfpwhsl.1=The Selection Expand item can increase or decrease the size of your selection window in all directions.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_oestvsz.vfpwhsl.2=To use the Selection expand item:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_oestvsz.vfpwhsl.3=1. §7Create a selection using the Selection Wand.§r 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_oestvsz.vfpwhsl.4=2. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block §7button while holding the Selection expand item to open an options menu.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_oestvsz.vfpwhsl.5=3. §7Move the §cAmount §7slider to the amount you would like to Expand or Contract your selection.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_oestvsz.vfpwhsl.6=4. §7Use the toggle to set the tool to Contract. By default it will Expand.§r 	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_oestvsz.vfpwhsl.7=5. §7Press the §cPerform Expand§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_oestvsz.vfpwhsl.8=Your selection will now be adjusted by the amount you set.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_oestvsz.vfpwhsl.9=Now that we have Selection Operations locked down we'll move onto the Shape Tools.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_oestvsz.jptaeut=Selection Expand	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_fill.vfpwhsl.1=The Selection Fill item, fills your selection with any block you have selected with the Block Picker.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_fill.vfpwhsl.2=To use the Selection Fill item:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_fill.vfpwhsl.3=1. §7Create a selection using the Selection Wand.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_fill.vfpwhsl.4=2. §7Pick a block you would like to use with the Block Picker.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_fill.vfpwhsl.5=3. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while holding the Selection Fill item.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_fill.vfpwhsl.6=Your selection will now be filled with your picked block.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_fill.vfpwhsl.7=Now that we can fill our Selection we'll move onto look at Selection Outline.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_fill.jptaeut=Selection Fill	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_move.vfpwhsl.1=The Selection Move item, moves a selection by a set amount of blocks, in the direction you are facing.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_move.vfpwhsl.yjcqsdz=To change this:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_move.vfpwhsl.uiwhyvv=1. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while §cSneaking§7 to open an additional options menu.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_move.vfpwhsl.qrwzkpp=2. §7Press the §cUpdate Selection§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_move.vfpwhsl.fanfouf=3. §7Press the §cPerform Move§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_move.vfpwhsl.qpksasl=Selections cannot be moved into unloaded chunks. You can maximise the range of the Selection Move item by standing between your selection and where you would like your selection to move.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_move.vfpwhsl.vrqpxni=We'll now look at Duplicating your selection with the Selection Stack.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_move.vfpwhsl.2=To use the Selection Move item:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_move.vfpwhsl.3=1. §7Create a selection using the Selection Wand.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_move.vfpwhsl.4=2. §7Face the direction you would like to move your selection.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_move.vfpwhsl.5=3. §7Press the §cUse Item / Place Block§7 button while holding the Selection Move item to open an options menu.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_move.vfpwhsl.6=4. §7Move the §cAmount§7 slider to the distance in blocks you would like your selection to move.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_move.vfpwhsl.7=5. §7Press the §cPerform Move§7 button.§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_move.vfpwhsl.8=Your selection will now be moved by the amount you set in the direction you are facing.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_move.vfpwhsl.9=By default your selection will also be moved along with the blocks.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_move.jptaeut=Selection Move	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.selection_ahqzwxt.vfpwhsl.1=§fSelection; Fill, Outline, Wall and Replace	#
