ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.1=The Whitelist allows Operators to grant and revoke World Builder access.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.yjcqsdz=§c/function oreville/wb/whitelist/status§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.uiwhyvv=§fGranting and Revoking Access:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.qrwzkpp=§7- When the whitelist is enabled, and if you are a World Builder Operator, you will see a new Player Permissions tab in the Handbook. This is where you can manage permissions!	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.fanfouf=§7- Click on a player's name, and use the toggles to change their permissions. After you click Submit, the changes will be applied.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.qpksasl=§7- The "World Builder Operator" permission will allow players to manage permissions of other players themselves.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.vrqpxni=§fTags:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.xclccmg=§7- Tags can also be used to control permissions. We recommend using the handbook, mentioned above, however, here is a list of tags, for advanced users.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.hqtfelu=§7- World Builder Operator:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.iyanacu=§c/tag @s add worldbuilder.op§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.fpdlmcv=§7- Grant access:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.2=When the Whitelist is enabled, only players who have been given explicit permission will be able to use World Builder's tools.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.xdnvfuf=§c/tag name add worldbuilder§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.vjnannn=§7- Revoke access:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.fqzcsma=§c/tag name remove worldbuilder§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.flzitzb=§7- Replace "name" with the player's name. These commands grant and revoke players access to all of World Builder's tools.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.aiqkzuo=§7- The player must be online for you to grant or revoke access using tags.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.usmrjbn=§fGranting and Revoking Access to specific features:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.xdykkrr=§7- You can customise which features of World Builder a player can use. Each action has its own permission, which can be granted or revoked using a tag.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.chbqktg=§7- Example: If you only want a player to have access to Brushes, Undo and Redo:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.knmvuwq=§c/tag name add worldbuilder.brush§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.jfdeqxa=§c/tag name add worldbuilder.history§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.3=Type the follow commands in the chat to control the whitelist.	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.fnykprd=§7- Example: If you want a player to have all permissions, except Brushes you can use a §c-§7 to disable that feature:	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.kzikwms=§c/tag name add worldbuilder§r	#
ui.oreville_wb:gbpmshn.whitelist.vfpwhsl.rrhimnl=§c/tag name add -worldbuilder.brush§r	#
